\is1 Study Notes
\ili1 1. By the grace of God, you now know that you have received Jesus and are God’s child; you must now take pains to make His salvation known. There is many a one who longs to know and cannot find out how he can become a child of God.
\ili1 2. Endeavour to make two things plain to him. First, that the new birth is something so high and holy that he can do nothing in it. He must receive eternal life from God through the Spirit. He must be born from above. This Jesus teaches \rq (John 3:1–8)\rq*.Then, make it clear to him how low God has descended to us with this new life, and how near He brings it to us. In Jesus there is life for everyone who believes in Him. This Jesus teaches \rq (John 3:14–18)\rq*. And Jesus and the life are in the Word.
\ili1 3. Tell the sinner that when he takes the Word, he then has Jesus and life in the Word \rq (Romans 10:8)\rq*. Take pains to tell the glad tidings that we become children of God only through faith in Jesus.
